Derek Skyler Brux, 22, was sentenced to five years probation for unhitching a train from a coal mine and crashing it into another train last fall . 
  He pleaded guilty to unhitching two locomotives and going on a high-speed run 13 miles down one of the busiest lines of track in the country . 
  Brux must also pay $63,000 in restitution to his employer Rail Link . 
  He was upset over a phone call he received from his boss . 
 